    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Architecture Deep-Dives</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">These appendices are the register-and-address-level companions to chapter 5 (Architecture &amp; Internals). Where chapter 5 explains a subsystem for an operator, the deep-dives name the V4 classes, the numeric IPR indices, the entry-vector offsets, and the source files -- the level a developer needs to read or extend the code.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Memory Map &amp; IPRs -- the physical address regions and the internal processor register space.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Addressing &amp; TLB -- the Ev6 translator, the SPAM shard manager, and TLB epoch invalidation.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Decompressor Internals -- the DEC inflate sources and the host_decompressor oracle.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Execution / Boot Internals -- the six-stage pipeline and fault entry vectors.</li>
    </list>
